This Image seems clearly to have been in the South Aisle of the Nave. The Will of Joan Golding in 1464 mentions an Image of Our Lady, but again we do not know the position of the tomb. William Gee in 1485 mentions an Image of the Virgin in the Nave3 but he was buried in the North Aisle. There was an Image of the Virgin in the Chapel of S. Mary : see Joan Elveden, 1420.
